      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T11:09:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Because redfish resources can\u0027t be present underneath multiple URIs.\n\nThe `cooling/cooled_by` directly determines resource placement currently.\n\nSo we would have something like\n\n```\nredfish/v1/Chassis/Yv3_Chassis_1/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/FAN_1\nredfish/v1/Chassis/Yv3_Chassis_1/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/FAN_2\n\nredfish/v1/Chassis/Yv3_Chassis_2/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/FAN_1\nredfish/v1/Chassis/Yv3_Chassis_2/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/FAN_2\n```\n\nWhich is not allowed in redfish from my understanding.\n\nAn alternative would be to use `cooling/cooled_by` for the resource placement as before and yet another association to determine which chassis the fan is actually cooling.\n\nBut that\u0027s conceptually wrong since bmcweb conventionally uses `containing` association to determine resource placement and the  `cooling` association describes a concept that\u0027s not `1:1`.\n\nIt\u0027s more like an `1:n` where one fan can be cooling multiple things.\n\nSo if we were to continue with the existing code it would be conceptually inconsistent in bmcweb and require introducing yet another association.",
      "parentUuid": "96e1036e_7d3de79b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "b80f6979b55934fc5208c2b9fdab8a5759e43d27",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
